Issues.Body:
I were testing the following css:

~~~ css
@layer tailwind {
  @tailwind base;
  @tailwind components;
  @tailwind utilities;
}

.foo {
  bar: "baz";
}
~~~

This would generate all the tailwind generated css on a real cascade layer named tailwind, and it does work as expected for most cases, but for some reason _some rules_ are generated outside of the layer and attached at the very end of the file instead:

For example: `text-black placeholder:text-red-200` on version `3.4.4` will generate: ([play](https://play.tailwindcss.com/YH2ly5iql6?file=css))

~~~ css
@layer tailwind {
  /* ! tailwindcss v3.4.4 | .. */
  .text-black {
    --tw-text-opacity: 1;
    color: rgb(0 0 0 / var(--tw-text-opacity));
  }
}
.foo {
  bar: "baz";
}
.placeholder\:text-red-200::placeholder {
  --tw-text-opacity: 1;
  color: rgb(254 202 202 / var(--tw-text-opacity));
}
~~~

Regards.

This makes things like `bg-gradient-[125deg]` and `bg-gradient-[1.3rad]` work. Now the output will be:

```css
.bg-gradient-\[1\.3rad\] {
  background-image: linear-gradient(1.3rad, var(--tw-gradient-stops, ));
}

.bg-gradient-\[125deg\] {
  background-image: linear-gradient(125deg, var(--tw-gradient-stops, ));
}
```

When using 0.5 as negative value, tailwind generates "-foo-0" as an extra class on the generated css.

Here is the reproduction of the issue on play: https://play.tailwindcss.com/5zq4jfVadZ using v3.4.3

~~~ html
<div class="fixed -inset-0.5 -left-0.5">Hy</div>
~~~

And the generated css ends with:

~~~ css
.-inset-0 {
  inset: -0px;
}
.-inset-0\.5 {
  inset: -0.125rem;
}
.-left-0 {
  left: -0px;
}
.-left-0\.5 {
  left: -0.125rem;
}
~~~

It is not a big bug in this case, just two extra lines on the css, but may be it have other escenarios with a bigger impact. Regards.

```js
// It works fine
{
  theme: {
    borderRadius: {
      DEFAULT: '10px'
    }
  }
}

// Its not possible
{
  theme: {
    extend: {
      borderRadius: {
        newProperty: "20px"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

tailwind version = "tailwindcss": "^3.4.3"

This PR fixes a backwards compatibility issue where the data type for `length` uses `background-position` instead of `background-size`:

v3:
```css
.bg-\[length\:50px_100px\] {
  background-size: 50px 100px;
}
```

v4 before this change:
```css
.bg-\[length\:50px_100px\] {
  background-position: 50px 100px;
}
```

v4 after this change:
```css
.bg-\[length\:50px_100px\] {
  background-size: 50px 100px;
}
```

